message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Fiji, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Bicycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, it can be a convenient and faster way to reach the grocery store. It will take around 3-5 minutes to cover the distance on a bicycle.

3. Public transportation: Check if there are any local buses or taxis available that can take you to the grocery store. Inquire about the nearest bus stop or taxi stand, and take a short ride to your destination.

4. Carpooling or ridesharing: If you have friends, neighbors, or colleagues who are heading to the grocery store, you can ask for a ride or organize a carpool. This way, you can share the transportation costs and reduce your carbon footprint.

Consider the available options based on your preferences, convenience, and the resources at your disposal.
